  "name": "RPlog_Interrogation_-_Tell_the_Truth",
  "title": "Tell the Truth, Captain Caiton",
  "summary": "Still bound by Luke Skywalker's Force command to answer honestly, the captured Imperial Captain Lynae Caiton is visited in her cell aboard the Reprisal by Captain Stone, a former Imperial Admiral who defected to the New Republic. The two spar over the soul of the Empire, Stone arguing that its current leadership has abandoned honor and purpose for the slaughter of civilians, and Caiton fiercely defending the Imperial vision while admitting she commanded the orbital bombardment of Etti IV and hates the Rebels with every fiber of her being. Watching the feed alongside the Sullustan official Enb'Zik, Luke notes her thorough indoctrination and arranges for her broken arm to be properly treated. Luke then conducts a private session, using the Force to compel Caiton's truthful answers about her role in torturing Brandis Finian and the chain of command behind it, learning that even she has never heard of Emperor Vadim. After showing her a Force-vision of the Sith terror to contrast with the New Republic's justice, and meeting only her insistence on perspective-based realities, Luke quietly apologizes and departs, the interrogation reaching its end.",
